headline: The New York Stock Exchange Leads Globally with over $60BN in Total Capital Raised During First Half of 2025
summary: NEW YORK, July 01, 2025--The New York Stock Exchange, part of Intercontinental Exchange, Inc. (NYSE: ICE), a leading global provider of technology and data, today reported an industry-leading $61 billion in total capital raised during the first half of 2025, up nearly 40% versus the same period last year.
